\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 31, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104vvy1665702863631.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vvy1665702863631.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vvy1665702863631.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"vvy1665702863631\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      &lt;x-entity&gt;\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"vvy1665702863631___x_entity__387611\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface-specific XHTML tag that defines the location and presentation format of an entity in the layout of a static server page.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"vvy1665702863631__topic_d115460e1_d115461e1_d115462e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vvy1665702863631__p_d115463e1_d115464e1_d115465e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;x-entity</code> {<code class=\"ph codeph\">exclude=\"0\"</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">\"1\"</code>} <code class=\"ph codeph\">name=\"</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">EntityName</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"&gt;</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Contents</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;/x-entity&gt;</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vvy1665702863631__topic_d81952e1_d81953e1_d81954e1_d81955e1_d81956e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d267934e84\">\n                       \n Arguments\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vvy1665702863631__li_d44030e1_d44031e1_d44032e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vvy1665702863631__p_d115469e1_d115470e1_d115471e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">exclude</code>—for compatibility with server pages created prior to Uniface 9.4. Determines whether the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">webgen</span> ProcScript statement should generate the <var class=\"keyword varname\">Contents</var> in the XHTML page sent to the browser. If specified, it overwrites the exclude specification in the parent <code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;x-entity&gt;</code> or <code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;x-occurrence&gt;</code>. The allowed values are <code class=\"ph codeph\">\"0\"</code> (<var class=\"keyword varname\">Contents</var> are generated) or <code class=\"ph codeph\">\"1\"</code> (<var class=\"keyword varname\">Contents</var> are not generated).</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vvy1665702863631__li_d44033e1_d44034e1_d44035e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vvy1665702863631__p_d115472e1_d115473e1_d115474e1\">\n                  EntityName —fully qualified and capitalized name of an entity, for example, <code class=\"ph codeph\">MY_ENTITY.MY_MODEL</code>\n</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vvy1665702863631__li_d44036e1_d44037e1_d44038e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vvy1665702863631__p_d115475e1_d115476e1_d115477e1\">\n                  Contents —one of the following:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vvy1665702863631__li_d44039e1_d44040e1_d44041e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vvy1665702863631__p_d115478e1_d115479e1_d115480e1\">Standard XHTML</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vvy1665702863631__li_d44042e1_d44043e1_d44044e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vvy1665702863631__p_d115481e1_d115482e1_d115483e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;x-subst&gt;</code> tags</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vvy1665702863631__li_d44045e1_d44046e1_d44047e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vvy1665702863631__p_d115484e1_d115485e1_d115486e1\">one <code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;x-occurrence&gt;</code> tag, defining iteration properties for the entity</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vvy1665702863631__li_d44048e1_d44049e1_d44050e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vvy1665702863631__p_d115487e1_d115488e1_d115489e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;x-entity&gt;</code> tags for all inner entities painted on a server page</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vvy1665702863631__topic_d81957e1_d81958e1_d81959e1_d81960e1_d81961e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d267934e178\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vvy1665702863631__p_d115493e1_d115494e1_d115495e1\">When copying or inserting Uniface objects into the server page layout, Uniface generates <code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;x-entity&gt;</code> tags for every entity you select. If you select the component and set the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Document Style</span> option to <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Data entry</span>, it is automatically inserted inside a <code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;form&gt;</code> element so that the data can be submitted.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vvy1665702863631__p_d115496e1_d115497e1_d115498e1\">If you insert an entity outside a <code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;form&gt;</code> tag, the data is displayed but it cannot be submitted.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vvy1665702863631__p_d115499e1_d115500e1_d115501e1\">If the entity does not need to be sent to a browser, do not insert it in the server page. Alternatively, set the <code class=\"ph codeph\">exclude</code> attribute on the <code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;x-entity&gt;</code> element to <code class=\"ph codeph\">\"1\"</code>, for example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">&lt;x-entity exclude=\"1\" name=\"MY_ENTITY.MY_MODEL\"&gt;\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/snh1704692180687.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Static Server Pages</a><p>Static Server Page (USP) components generate a complete web page every time they are activated. This makes them useful for relatively static web pages or a thin-client architecture in which all processing is done on the server. They can also be used for RESTful applications or file upload functionality.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hxr1705401640523.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Insert Uniface Objects in the Server Page Layout</a><p>When creating the layout, elements in the layout must be bound to the component data structure as defined in the Component Editor. You can do this by copying the Uniface objects from the component structure and inserting them as HTML in the layout.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gna1665702540285.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>webgen</a><p>Generate an XHTML document from the layout definition and the component definition of a static server page.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jvt1719471343733.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Layout of Static Server Pages</a><p>Static server page layouts are XHTML-based and include Uniface-specific tags to define the component data structure, as well as standard XHTML for defining the layout and appearance. The structure of the layout is best viewed in the XHTML source.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533209\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533209\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "<x-entity> Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 31, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 <x-entity> Uniface-specific XHTML tag that defines the location and presentation format of an entity in the layout of a static server page. <x-entity { exclude=\"0\" | \"1\" } name=\" EntityName \"> Contents </x-entity> Arguments exclude —for compatibility with server pages created prior to Uniface 9.4. Determines whether the webgen ProcScript statement should generate the Contents in the XHTML page sent to the browser. If specified, it overwrites the exclude specification in the parent <x-entity> or <x-occurrence> . The allowed values are \"0\" ( Contents are generated) or \"1\" ( Contents are not generated). EntityName —fully qualified and capitalized name of an entity, for example, MY_ENTITY.MY_MODEL Contents —one of the following: Standard XHTML <x-subst> tags one <x-occurrence> tag, defining iteration properties for the entity <x-entity> tags for all inner entities painted on a server page Description When copying or inserting Uniface objects into the server page layout, Uniface generates <x-entity> tags for every entity you select. If you select the component and set the Document Style option to Data entry , it is automatically inserted inside a <form> element so that the data can be submitted. If you insert an entity outside a <form> tag, the data is displayed but it cannot be submitted. If the entity does not need to be sent to a browser, do not insert it in the server page. Alternatively, set the exclude attribute on the <x-entity> element to \"1\" , for example: <x-entity exclude=\"1\" name=\"MY_ENTITY.MY_MODEL\"> Copy Related Links Static Server Pages Static Server Page (USP) components generate a complete web page every time they are activated. This makes them useful for relatively static web pages or a thin-client architecture in which all processing is done on the server. They can also be used for RESTful applications or file upload functionality. Insert Uniface Objects in the Server Page Layout When creating the layout, elements in the layout must be bound to the component data structure as defined in the Component Editor. You can do this by copying the Uniface objects from the component structure and inserting them as HTML in the layout. webgen Generate an XHTML document from the layout definition and the component definition of a static server page. Layout of Static Server Pages Static server page layouts are XHTML-based and include Uniface-specific tags to define the component data structure, as well as standard XHTML for defining the layout and appearance. The structure of the layout is best viewed in the XHTML source. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}